Commentary Text: Chris Morris to Tymal Mills, out Bowled!! Morris gets another wicket with a juicy full-toss. RCB finish with just 157 on the board. Mills made room on the drive, missed and the off-stump goes for a walk. Tymal Mills b Chris Morris 0(3)
team_a_11: Royal Challengers Bangalore (Playing XI): Chris Gayle, Mandeep Singh, Vishnu Vinod(w), Kedar Jadhav, Shane Watson(c), Stuart Binny, Pawan Negi, Iqbal Abdulla, Tymal Mills, Yuzvendra Chahal, Billy Stanlake
team_b_11: Delhi Daredevils (Playing XI): Sam Billings, Aditya Tare, Sanju Samson, Karun Nair, Rishabh Pant(w), Carlos Brathwaite, Chris Morris, Pat Cummins, Shahbaz Nadeem, Zaheer Khan(c), Amit Mishra
toss: RCB won the toss and opted to bat first at the Chinnaswamy. That's a brave call, they are playing three spinners as well. Are they hoping for the bowlers to defend whatever their batsmen make? We are ready for Bengaluru's first IPL 10 game..

Commentary Text: Zaheer to Kedar Jadhav, out Caught by Chris Morris!! That's another huge wicket and RCB are losing their way towards the end. Lovely piece of deception from Zaheer. He followed the slower short ball with another slower ball, rolled his fingers across the seam. Kedar was backing away on the lofted drive, gets it right off the bottom of the bat, plenty of height but not the distance. Morris settles under it and holds on at mid-off. Commentary Text: Zaheer to Vishnu Vinod, out Vishnu Vinod Run Out!! That was completely unnecessary from Vishnu Vinod and it has cost him his wicket. team_a_11: Royal Challengers Bangalore (Playing XI): Chris Gayle, Mandeep Singh, Vishnu Vinod(w), Kedar Jadhav, Shane Watson(c), Stuart Binny, Pawan Negi, Iqbal Abdulla, Tymal Mills, Yuzvendra Chahal, Billy Stanlake

toss: RCB won the toss and opted to bat first at the Chinnaswamy. That's a brave call, they are playing three spinners as well. Are they hoping for the bowlers to defend whatever their batsmen make? They are still without VK and AB, they have lost KL. Tough times if you are a RCB fan. Gayle and a change at the top - it's Watson who's walking out to the middle. We are ready for Bengaluru's first IPL 10 game..
winner: Royal Challengers Bangalore won by 15 runs
